title: Caitlyn Jenner won't be charged in fatal car accident
text:

By Sadie Gennis, 
Caitlyn Jenner will not be charged with vehicular manslaughter or any crime stemming from the fatal crash, TMZ reports. 
The L.A. County D.A. declared that Jenner was not speeding at the time her vehicle rear-ended the victim's car in February. While it was acknowledged that Jenner hit the brakes belatedly, the D.A. said they couldn't prove her conduct was "unreasonable." 
I Am Cait will return for a second season 
"We believed from the start that a thorough and objective investigation would clear Caitlyn of any criminal wrongdoing." Jenner's lawyer Blair Berk told the website. "We are heartened the District Attorney has agreed that even a misdemeanor charge would not be appropriate. A traffic accident, however devastating and heartbreaking when a life is lost, is not necessarily a criminal matter."
